<br>
There's no conspiracy here.  The EQ formula seemed ok in the beginning and has held people's attention all of this time; if it ain't broke, don't fix it.<br>
<br>
If all of the upcoming competition hurts EQ's subscriber base and it seems to be a result of the game mechanic, they will go through pains to change it.  If the competition does not cause a decrease in EQ subscribership, they will assume that there is still a healthy player-base that enjoys the game mechanic and stick with it.  None of this is a mystery, to be honest, and it seems pretty logical to me. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uchukzombi.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Chukzombi</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://chukzombi.homestead.com/files/usa5_2.gif   " BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Undead Shaman</span><br>  Posts: 2004<br> <font color=#E9D756>(10/1/01 2:34:43 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://chukzombi.homestead.com/files/chukundead.jpg 60x60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: heh</span><hr size=1> Do the original Paw of Oppala  or the RoLT quest and  ask yourself if this isnt intentional.<br>
The rewards go to the person who spends the most time in eq. Thats the way its always been thats the way it always will be, any quest you find that gives a great reward with minimal time spent is due for a nerf.<br>
Scout Charisa anyone?<br>
<br>
I dont really agree with that idea but i understand  where they are coming from. If you wish to have a CoF you must get 30-40  people together form a raifd and work your way through Fgs and then kill Lord Nagafen. Even then its not a given a CoF will drop or let alone that you will receive it. this is a time sink but a necesary one. I do find it rather stupid from a RP stance that you must kill the same dragon every week to work him to get the prizes all of your crew wants.<br>
Maybe like Sudo suggested in IRC today, make a pool of 10 different dragons on the same spawn and each time you fight lord nag hes a dif dragon , this makes things more interesting and not seem like such a time sink.<br>
