I really hated solo camping and didn't see the point in wasting my time.<br>
<br>
It's ridiculous what it takes to get anything out of this game.  You either have to do the above and spend many many many hours camping various mobs, or you get to kill all these &quot;uber&quot; mobs that everyone else wants to kill and you usually get to butt heads with others which leads to the rants and flames you see here.  It's always nice to get that awesome BP or that &quot;uber&quot; weapon, but it just gets to a point where it's not worth the hassle anymore.<br>
<br>
I can certainly understand things from Verant's point of view.  They want people to play as much and as long as possible because it means more money for them.  Don't believe for a second that they are doing this for you, they are doing this for them.  Sure, they could up spawn rates, increase drop rates, but that means you get what you want sooner and that's bad business for them.  Sure, it would make the game more fun if more than 4 people out of 40 could get a Vindi drop and it would certainly help to balance out the risk vs. reward a little more, but they'd rather you stuck around, no matter how much you have to butt heads with others contesting spawns or how many hours of your life you waste trying to get a lousy gold ring.<br>
<br>
I highly recommend everybody quit and play something else.  If you really want to make a statement that Verant will pay attention to, that's the only way to go.  Everything else is just blowing smoke.  Yes, I realize it's not very likely that will happen.  This game is too addicting and I had the almost 200 played days to prove it, but wouldn't you just love to be at the VI offices the day after everyone cancels their account? <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><a href=http://www.afflictionguild.com/profile.php?username=Carathos&charactername=Carathos>Carathos Ollathir<BR><a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bthedruidsgrove> 60th Druid<BR> <a href=http://www.afflictionguild.com/>~Affliction~</a>
